#Lyrics
Eternal Father, strong to save, Whose arm hath bound the restless wave, Who bidd'st the mighty ocean deep Its own appointed limits keep; O hear us when we cry to Thee For those in peril on the sea.  2. O Christ, whose voice the waters heard And hushed their raging at Thy word, Who walkedst on the foaming deep, And calm amidst its rage didst keep; O hear us when we cry to Thee For those in peril on the sea.  3. O Holy Spirit, who didst brood Upon the waters dark and rude, And bid their angry tumult cease, And give, for wild confusion, peace; O hear us when we cry to Thee For those in peril on the sea.  4. O Trinity of love and power, Our people shield in danger's hour; From rock and tempest, fire and foe, Guard them where'er they may go; Thus evermore shall rise to Thee Glad hymns of praise from land and sea.

